This is UmmahConnect — a Next.js 14 App Router project for Muslim professionals in Nigeria.

Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, Auth.js, React Query, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS, Zod, Lucide React.

Design system:
- Primary: #1A6B5C (Forest Teal)
- Accent: #C9A84C (Warm Gold)
- Dark background: #0D1B1E
- Secondary dark: #132420
- Light background: #FAF7F2
- Muted on dark: rgba(255,255,255,0.45)
- Success/halal: #5ECDB5
- Headings: Playfair Display, 700/900
- Body: DM Sans, 300/400/500/600

Rules:
- Never use `any` types
- Never use default Tailwind blue or grey
- All API routes must use withHandler from src/lib/api/helpers.ts
- All inputs validated with Zod from src/lib/validation.ts
- Use auth() server-side from @/lib/auth, useSession() client-side from next-auth/react
- Nigeria is the only country in Phase 1
- All colours from the design system above only
